@node main "CYCAS DEMO Help - Screen"
@toc "help.guide/main"


  Modifying the Cycas screen:


  Starting CYCAS for the  first  time,  the  program  will
  adapt  the  screenmode of your workbench. You can change
  the screenmode you want to work in by pressing the right
  mouse  button  (pull down  menus) and selecting the menu
  GUI setup: After you have changed the screenmode of  the
  CYCAS  screen you can adjust the following from the same
  pull down menu.


  Font:
  You can change the screen font. Avoid using  large  font
  sizes as they may not fit the user interface .


  Screenmode:
  Choose your preferred screenmode.


  Palette:
  You can alter the user interface colours.


  -Original:
  Reverts to the original CYCAS color setup.


  Screen ratio:
  Adapting  the  screen  ratio  to   the   chosen   screen
  resolution. Measure the horizontal and vertical distance
  of the window in "cm" and enter  the  results  into  the
  width-  and  depth  gadget.  If you leave the window the
  screen ratio should be installed correctly.


  Save:
  Save the setup.

@endnode
